  carbohydrates: 40 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 770 mg
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-homestyle-creamy-chicken-bake-6682ed1bb46c5c38d61d4fd5
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Pat @riced cauliflower{6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise into quarters; slice into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

== Cauliflower-Parm Topping ==

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in cauliflower rice, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Set aside until ready to use in Step 5.

== Chicken and Veggies ==

Pat @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), salt, and pepper to pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add carrots, scallion whites, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies begin to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Return chicken to pan. Evenly sprinkle @flour{2%tablespoon} over chicken and veggies and cook, stirring, until no lumps remain, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add 1 1/4 cups @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 1/2 cups for 4) and @chicken stock concentrate{2}. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir in @peas{4%ounce} and @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Smooth chicken and veggie mixture out in an even layer with the back of a #spoon{}. If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling to an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (13-by-9-inch baking dish for 4) now.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, use a baking dish for the final baking step.

Sprinkle with cauliflower-Parmesan topping.

Bake on top rack until topping is golden brown, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Garnish chicken bake with scallion greens. Divide between plates or serve family style directly from pan.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.